<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-203-241 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 432 517</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  March 11 1991 v13 n10 p68(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CA-SuperProject 2.0: a top corporate project manager. (SoftwareReview) (Computer Associates International Inc.'s projectmanagement software) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Heck, Mike.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Computer Associates International Inc's CA-SuperProject 2.0 offersa more graphical interface and is easier to use than earlierversions, making it appropriate for smaller businesses andless-experienced users while retaining the powerful functions thatallow it to serve corporate needs.andP;  The package is rated excellentin features and flexibility; users can build tree diagrams andPERT network diagrams, with emphasis on resource management.andP;  Theuser can allocate unlimited resources for each project andworkgroup, and unlimited assignments for each task.andP;  Reschedulingand resource leveling are very good; there are 1,000 prioritylevels available.andP;  Speed is rated good, and reporting is verygood.andP;  The program offers very good documentation, includingon-line help and a reference card.andP;  Ease of learning is good,while ease of use is very good.andP;  Error handling earns a 'good'rating.andP;  Computer Associates' support policies are rated good, butthe support itself is only satisfactory.andP;  CA-SuperProject 2.0 israted a very good value for its price of $895.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Computer Associates International Inc. (Products).andO;Ticker:    CA.andO;Product:   CA-SuperProject 2.0 (Project management software).andO;Topic:     Project Management SystemsSoftware PackagesEvaluation.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Report card. (table)Mainstream project management software comparative benchmarks.andO;(table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>